PN,31702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,FWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so
OL,8,Fimportant, and how could prolonged
OL,9,Fdisruption affect the global economy
OL,10,Fand UK bills?
OL,12,FWhat is the Strait of Hormuz?
OL,14,FThe Strait of Hormuz is a narrow
OL,15,Fpassage that connects the Persian Gulf
OL,16,Fto the Gulf of Oman.
OL,18,FIran controls the entire northern
OL,19,Fside, effectively allowing it to wield
OL,20,Fthe strait as a geopolitical
OL,21,Fchokepoint.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,FThe strait ` almost 100 miles long and
OL,8,F21 miles wide at its narrowest point `
OL,9,Fallows some of the world's largest
OL,10,Fvessels to transport a fifth of global
OL,11,Foil and gas supplies.
OL,13,FShips departing to or from Kuwait,
OL,14,FBahrain, Qatar and the United Arab
OL,15,FEmirates must pass through the strait
OL,16,Fto reach open waters.
OL,18,FCrude oil from Saudi Arabia, Iraq and
OL,19,FIran is also transported through the
OL,20,Fpassage.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,FWhen it comes to moving oil, the
OL,8,Fstrait is actually much narrower than
OL,9,Fits 21-mile official width.
OL,11,FThe navigable shipping lanes for
OL,12,Fmassive supertankers are only about
OL,13,Ftwo miles wide in each direction,
OL,14,Frequiring vessels to pass through both
OL,15,FIranian and Omani territorial waters.
OL,17,FAny disruption to traffic through the
OL,18,FStrait of Hormuz is, in turn, highly
OL,19,Fdisruptive to the oil trade.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,FWhat has Iran said about the Strait
OL,8,Fsince the conflict sparked again?
OL,10,FThe Strait of Hormuz is effectively
OL,11,Fclosed. Iran has carried out attacks
OL,12,Fon ships passing through and vowed to
OL,13,Fcontinue this, which has led to
OL,14,Fshipping companies suspending
OL,15,Foperations in the area.
OL,17,FOn Monday, a senior adviser to Iran's
OL,18,FRevolutionary Guard threatened anyone
OL,19,Fwho might attempt to pass through the
OL,20,Fstrait.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,F"The Strait of Hormuz is closed.
OL,8,FAnyone who wants to pass, our devotee
OL,9,Fheroes in the IRGC navy and the army
OL,10,Fwill set those ships on fire," he
OL,11,Fsaid. "Don't come to this region."
OL,13,FThey also threatened that Iran will
OL,14,F"attack oil pipelines" and "not allow
OL,15,Fa single drop of oil to leave the
OL,16,Fregion".
OL,18,FWhat is the disruption?
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@^O]sD@GOUsD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,FOver 3,000 ships are estimated to be
OL,8,Fstranded around the strait, with
OL,9,Faround 150 of these being tankers that
OL,10,Fcarry oil.
OL,12,FThe number of tankers is roughly twice
OL,13,Fas many as usual, according to data
OL,14,Fand analytics firm Kplr, indicating a
OL,15,Fhalting of trade movements as ships
OL,16,Fhave nowhere to go.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,FSeveral ships are believed to have
OL,8,Fbeen attacked by Iran, including a
OL,9,FMarshall Islands-flagged oil tanker in
OL,10,Fthe Gulf of Oman, which killed one
OL,11,Fmariner.
OL,13,FTanker traffic has dropped sharply, as
OL,14,Fglobal shippers suspend operations in
OL,15,Fthe area until further notice.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,F"No one wants to navigate it, and
OL,8,Fthere's no insurer who's willing to
OL,9,Fstand behind any transport going
OL,10,Fthrough there right now," said Tom
OL,11,FGoldsby, logistics chairman in the
OL,12,FSupply Chain Management Department at
OL,13,Fthe University of Tennessee.
OL,15,F"Those ships that got stuck in the
OL,16,FGulf are not going anywhere. ...
OL,17,FThere's also a whole host of ships
OL,18,Fthat were heading into the Gulf to
OL,19,Freplace them, and of course they're
OL,20,Fanchored or going elsewhere now."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,FWho would be hit hardest?
OL,9,FSeveral countries could be impacted,
OL,10,Fparticularly Saudi Arabia, the UAE,
OL,11,Fand Kuwait, China, India, Japan, the
OL,12,FUS, and South Korea.
OL,14,FA closure of the strait would be
OL,15,Fparticularly detrimental to China and
OL,16,Fother Asian economies, which rely on
OL,17,Fthe crude oil and natural gas shipped
OL,18,Fthrough the waterway.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,FThe Energy Information Administration
OL,8,F(EIA) estimates that 84% of the crude
OL,9,Foil and 83% of the liquefied natural
OL,10,Fgas that moved through the Strait of
OL,11,FHormuz in 2024 went to Asian markets.
OL,13,FHow have the markets responded?
OL,15,FBrent crude, the international
OL,16,Fstandard, rose again on Tuesday,
OL,17,Ftaking it to a one-year high of nearly
OL,18,F81 US dollars a barrel. Overall, an
OL,19,Fincrease of 13% since fighting broke
OL,20,Fout on Saturday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,FGas prices have also surged at the
OL,8,Ffastest pace since the outbreak of war
OL,9,Fin Ukraine. They were up 52%, after
OL,10,FQatar halted production of liquified
OL,11,Fnatural gas on Monday following
OL,12,Fattacks by Iran. They rose again by
OL,13,Fanother 20% on Tuesday.
OL,15,FStock markets have also tumbled across
OL,16,Fthe UK and Europe, as fears of a
OL,17,Fprolonged conflict begin to set in.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31713
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,FSusannah Streeter, chief investment
OL,8,Fstrategist at the Wealth Club, said:
OL,9,F"London's FTSE 100 has fallen deeper
OL,10,Finto the red as the war widens and
OL,11,Fcompanies assess the impact of severe
OL,12,Fdisruption across the region on their
OL,13,Foperations."
OL,15,FRichard Hunter, head of markets at
OL,16,FInteractive Investor, said the easing
OL,17,Fin the pace of the oil price rally
OL,18,Fsuggests "a more sanguine approach to
OL,19,Fthe implications of the US/Iran
OL,20,Fsituation".
OL,26,@qD@AOUuD@LO]zD@JOU|D@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31714
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,F"Oil price spikes usually follow
OL,8,Fconflict outbreaks, but the fact
OL,9,Fremains that escalation and duration
OL,10,Fis more of a concern than the
OL,11,Fimmediate outlook," he said.
OL,13,FThe impact on fuel prices has already
OL,14,Fbeen acute, and the blockage of the
OL,15,FStrait of Hormuz caused the cost of
OL,16,Fhiring an oil supertanker to carry
OL,17,Fcrude from the Middle East to China to
OL,18,Freach an all-time high on Monday of
OL,19,Fnearly #300,000.
OL,21,FWhat could it mean for UK energy bills?
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31715
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,FThe price increases could impact UK
OL,8,Fhouseholds in the coming months if
OL,9,Fpetrol prices and domestic energy
OL,10,Fbills surge.
OL,12,FBills are protected by Ofgem's price
OL,13,Fcap until 1 July 2026, as the cap from
OL,14,FApril to June has already been set.
OL,16,FSimon Francis, coordinator of the End
OL,17,FFuel Poverty Coalition, explains that
OL,18,Fthe price cap "works by smoothing out
OL,19,Fprice spikes and delaying the passing
OL,20,Fon of cost increases to consumers".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31716
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,F"But that also means the real risk is
OL,8,Fwhat happens next. If elevated prices
OL,9,Fpersist, they will affect Ofgem's next
OL,10,Fprice cap decision in May, which takes
OL,11,Feffect from July.
OL,13,F"It is also unclear how suppliers will
OL,14,Frespond in the fixed tariff market. In
OL,15,Fperiods of uncertainty, they often
OL,16,Fwithdraw or increase the price of
OL,17,Fdeals to avoid exposure to volatile
OL,18,Fwholesale costs.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31717
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,F"Households that rely on heating oil
OL,8,Fare even more exposed, and the latest
OL,9,Fsurge in those prices will be a major
OL,10,Fconcern for rural and off-grid
OL,11,Ffamilies needing to refill in the
OL,12,Fcoming weeks.
OL,14,F"This is a stark reminder that the UK
OL,15,Fis still dangerously exposed to
OL,16,Fvolatile international markets.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31718
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772568683
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,F"The only lasting protection for
OL,8,Fhouseholds is to cut gas demand
OL,9,Fthrough a nationwide insulation
OL,10,Fprogramme, expand homegrown renewables
OL,11,Fand reform energy pricing so bills are
OL,12,Fno longer tied so closely to global
OL,13,Ffossil fuel prices."
